import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <BaseHead title="Ergonomics: Comfortable Setup & Peripherals - LaptopVette" description="Best practices for ergonomic laptop use, including posture, accessories, and recommended keyboards and mice." path="/guides/ergonomics" />
</head>
<body>
  <main class="container" style="padding:40px 20px;">
    <h1>Ergonomics: Comfortable Laptop Use and Recommended Peripherals</h1>
    <p>Long-term comfort and reducing strain depend on setup and peripherals. Laptops are inherently compact, so adding the right accessories and following posture best practices makes a big difference.</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Basic Setup Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Raise the screen so the top third of the display is at eye level using a stand.</li>
        <li>Use an external keyboard and mouse to keep wrists neutral and shoulders relaxed.</li>
        <li>Keep the laptop at a comfortable distance (roughly an arm's length) from your eyes.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Recommended Peripherals</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ergonomic keyboards with negative tilt or tenting options to reduce wrist extension.</li>
        <li>Vertical or sculpted mice that reduce pronation and wrist strain.</li>
        <li>Adjustable laptop stands and external monitors for multi-screen setups.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Accessories For Students & Home Offices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Portable lap desks for flexible posture when working on the couch.</li>
        <li>Lightweight external keyboards for longer typing sessions.</li>
        <li>Bluetooth mice with good battery life for mobility.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top:20px;">Want specific model suggestions? I can recommend ergonomic keyboards and mice at different price points and link to current pricing.</p>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
